A COP was shot in a cash-in-transit heist at the Durban CBD on Wednesday, 21 April. Paramedics responded to a call about a shooting incident near a popular shopping mall at Dr AB Xuma Street. A male police officer had suffered a gunshot wound to his chest and was in a serious condition. They said advanced life support emergency care practitioners worked to stabilise him. He was rushed to a nearby hospital. Paramedics said reports from the scene indicate the cop took fire from a number of armed suspects during an attempted robbery. Paramedics said police will investigate the matter.